  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a four-byte tag used to identify font tables, variation axes, and other OpenType resources.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFourByteTag` wraps a 32-bit unsigned integer whose four bytes are interpreted as ASCII characters. The tag `'w','g','h','t'` corresponds to `0x77676874`, matching the OpenType `wght` (weight) axis tag convention. Use the char-based constructor or `Parse` to create tags from readable string literals.

## Examples

```csharp
var wght = new SKFourByteTag('w', 'g', 'h', 't');
Console.WriteLine(wght.ToString()); // "wght"

var tag = SKFourByteTag.Parse("ital");
Console.WriteLine((uint)tag);       // 0x6974616C
```
]]></format></remarks>
